    "Fry criticized the German model of art scholarship in 1933 as seeing works of art \"almost entirely from a chronological point of view, as coefficients of a time sequence, without reference to their aesthetic significance.\"": [],
    "Fry's populist approach to art became so pervasive that some thirty years later the German-American art historian <a href=\"/wittkowerr\">Rudolf Wittkower</a> decried it in his own lecture, \"Art History as a Discipline.\"": [],
